<br>
I'd just bought the spell &quot;Befriend Animal.&quot;  For those of you who don't know, Befriend Animal charms an animal so it will do your bidding, evil or otherwise.  I hadn't ever tried the spell before, so I cast it on something unambitious -- a large rat.<br>
<br>
The rat shuffled to my side and stood there squeaking.  Being a druid, I had no idea how to control a pet, and as I stood there wondering what to do next, a bixie attacked me.<br>
<br>
Quickly, I asked the rat to attack the bixie -- and he did!  But the bixie was strong.  Standing a few feet away, I healed the rat a couple of times as it fought.  <br>
<br>
Suddenly I became aware of halfling voices behind me.  &quot;Two gold on the rat!&quot; said someone.  &quot;No way.  I'll give anyone three to one for the bixie!&quot; said another voice.<br>
<br>
I turned to find four or five very young halflings behind me.  They'd been watching, and now they were all wagering their hard-earned gold pieces on the outcome of the rat-bixie fight.  &quot;No fair healing the rat!&quot; one of them shouted.  &quot;Yeah Gwion,&quot; another one chimed in, &quot;I need this money for a new staff!&quot; <br>
<br>
After the winning bettors collected (the rat won, by the way), the halflings surrounded me, begging me to charm more animals and start another bout.  &quot;We don't want to hunt,&quot; they said, &quot;This is so much more fun!&quot;  I had nothing to do, so the group of us burnt a good portion of that afternoon on the animal contests.<br>
<br>
That's the truth about halflings -- they love to gamble!<br>
<br>
Gwion <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/udespaire.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Despaire</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>   <font color=#006400>(8/17/00 2:47:22 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The Truth About Halflings...</span><hr size=1> *ROFL* <br>
